{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/adopting-common-protocols","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"title":"Adopting Common Protocols","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Data Modeling","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes"],"anchor":"Data-Modeling"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using custom types to model data in your programs, you may frequently need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"check whether two values are the same or different, or whether a particular value","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is included in a list of values. This capability, as well as the ability to store","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values in a set or use them as keys in a dictionary, are governed by two related","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"standard library protocols, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can compare instances of an "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"equatable","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" type by using the equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":") and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not-equal-to ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"!="},{"text":") operators.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An instance of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hashable"}]},{"type":"text","text":" type can reduce its value mathematically to a single"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integer, which is used internally by sets and dictionaries to make lookups consistently"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"fast."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Many standard library types are both equatable and hashable, including strings, integers,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"floating-point values, Boolean values, and collections of equatable and hashable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" comparison and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"contains(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method call in the following example"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"depend on strings and integers being equatable:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["if username == \"Arturo\" {","    print(\"Hi, Arturo!\")","}","","let favoriteNumbers = [4, 7, 8, 9]","if favoriteNumbers.contains(todaysDate.day) {","    print(\"It's a good day today!\")","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Conforming to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocols is straightforward and makes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it easier to use your own types in Swift. It’s a good idea for all your custom model","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"types to conform."}]},{"level":3,"text":"Conform Automatically to Equatable and Hashable","type":"heading","anchor":"Conform-Automatically-to-Equatable-and-Hashable"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can make many custom types equatable and hashable by simply declaring these protocol"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conformances in the same file as the type’s original declaration. Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to the list of adopted protocols when declaring the type, and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"compiler automatically fills in the requirements for the two protocols:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/\/ A position in an x-y coordinate system.","struct Position: Equatable, Hashable {","    var x: Int","    var y: Int","","    init(_ x: Int, _ y: Int) {","        self.x = x","        self.y = y","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" conformance, you can use the equal-to operator (","type":"text"},{"code":"==","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") or the not-equal-to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operator ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"!="},{"type":"text","text":") with any two instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Position"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let availablePositions = [Position(0, 0), Position(0, 1), Position(1, 0)]","let gemPosition = Position(1, 0)","","for position in availablePositions {","    if gemPosition == position {","        print(\"Gem found at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))!\")","    } else {","        print(\"No gem at (\\(position.x), \\(position.y))\")","    }","}","\/\/ No gem at (0, 0)","\/\/ No gem at (0, 1)","\/\/ Gem found at (1, 0)!",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance means that you can store positions in a set and quickly check"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether you’ve visited a position before, as shown in the following example:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["var visitedPositions: Set = [Position(0, 0), Position(1, 0)]","let currentPosition = Position(1, 3)","","if visitedPositions.contains(currentPosition) {","    print(\"Already visited (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","} else {","    print(\"First time at (\\(currentPosition.x), \\(currentPosition.y))\")","    visitedPositions.insert(currentPosition)","}","\/\/ First time at (1, 3)",""],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition to simplifying your code, this automatic conformance reduces errors,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"because any new properties you add to your custom types are automatically included","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when hashing and testing for equality. A type is eligible for automatic conformance","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"type":"text","text":" when it’s a structure or an enumeration that meets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these criteria:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For a structure, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" its stored properties must conform to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For an enumeration, "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" its associated values must conform to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". (Enumerations without associated values have ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Hashable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conformance even without declaring adoption.)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Conform Manually to Equatable and Hashable","anchor":"Conform-Manually-to-Equatable-and-Hashable","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to manually implement "},{"code":"Equatable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" conformance for a type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in these cases:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The type doesn’t meet the criteria listed in the previous section.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You want to customize the type’s conformance.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You want to extend a type declared in another file or module to conform.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["class Player {","    var name: String","    var position: Position","","    init(name: String, position: Position) {","        self.name = name","        self.position = position","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"text":" type is a class, so it doesn’t qualify for automatic synthesis of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" requirements. To make this class conform to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Equatable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"protocol, declare conformance in an extension and implement the  static ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" operator","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. Compare each significant property for equality in your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method’s implementation:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension Player: Equatable {","    static func ==(lhs: Player, rhs: Player) -> Bool {","        return lhs.name == rhs.name && lhs.position == rhs.position","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To make ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"text":" conform to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" protocol, declare conformance in another","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"extension and implement the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":" method. In the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":" method, call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combine(_:)"},{"text":" method on the provided hasher with each significant property:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension Player: Hashable {","    func hash(into hasher: inout Hasher) {","        hasher.combine(name)","        hasher.combine(position)","    }","}"]},{"text":"Use All Significant Properties for Equatable and Hashable","level":3,"anchor":"Use-All-Significant-Properties-for-Equatable-and-Hashable","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When implementing the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method and the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":" method, use all the properties","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that affect whether two instances of your custom type are considered equal. In the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementations above, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Player"},{"text":" type uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"position"},{"text":" in both methods.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your type contains properties that don’t affect whether two instances are considered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"equal, exclude those properties from comparison in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"text":" method and from hashing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"text":". For example, a type might cache an expensive computed value so","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that it only needs to calculate it once. If you compare two instances of that type,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether or not the computed value has been cached shouldn’t affect their equality,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so the cached value should be excluded from comparison and hashing.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always use the same properties in both your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"=="},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hash(into:)"},{"type":"text","text":" methods."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Using different groups of properties in the two methods can lead to unexpected behavior"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or performance when using your custom type in sets and dictionaries."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/adopting-common-protocols"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Make your custom types easier to use by ensuring that they conform to Swift protocols."}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/choosing-between-structures-and-classes":{"type":"topic","title":"Choosing Between Structures and Classes","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes","kind":"article","role":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Decide how to store data and model behavior.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/choosing-between-structures-and-classes"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Hashable":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that can be hashed into a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hasher"},{"text":" to produce an integer hash value.","type":"text"}],"title":"Hashable","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Hashable","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/hashable","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Hashable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Hashable"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Equatable":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Equatable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Equatable","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Equatable","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/equatable","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A type that can be compared for value equality.","type":"text"}],"title":"Equatable"},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swift","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Build apps using a powerful open language.","type":"text"}],"title":"Swift"}}}